OL,3,CInfected-blood victims 'distressed and
OL,4,Cpowerless' over compensation scheme
OL,6,FThe victims and families of those
OL,7,Faffected by the infected-blood scandal
OL,8,Fhave been left feeling distressed and
OL,9,Fpowerless at the Government's approach
OL,10,Fto compensation, according to the
OL,11,Fchairman of the inquiry that
OL,12,Fscrutinised the treatment disaster.
OL,14,FIt comes as Sir Brian Langstaff said
OL,15,Fhe intends to publish a further report
OL,16,Flooking at the timeliness and adequacy
OL,17,Fof the Government's response.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/15
