OL,3,CInfected-blood victims 'distressed and
OL,4,Cpowerless' over compensation scheme
OL,6,FMore than 30,000 people in the UK were
OL,7,Finfected with HIV and hepatitis C
OL,8,Fafter they were given contaminated
OL,9,Fblood and blood products between the
OL,10,F1970s and early 1990s.
OL,12,FSome 3,000 people died as a result and
OL,13,Fsurvivors are living with lifelong
OL,14,Fhealth implications.
OL,16,FThe Infected Blood Inquiry published
OL,17,Fits final report on the scandal in May
OL,18,Flast year, and a compensation scheme
OL,19,Fwas announced a day later.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/15
