OL,3,CInfected-blood victims 'distressed and
OL,4,Cpowerless' over compensation scheme
OL,6,FWitnesses described not being listened
OL,7,Fto by the IBCA, and one statement
OL,8,Fexpressed concerns about allegations
OL,9,Fthat the Government is trying to
OL,10,F"silence" the community "to avoid
OL,11,Fembarrassment over the delays in the
OL,12,Frelease of compensation".
OL,14,F"I fear that the same institutional
OL,15,Fdefensiveness and groupthink that
OL,16,Fcaused the original scandal's cover-up
OL,17,Fare now hindering the scheme," they
OL,18,Fadded.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/15
