OL,4,Cpowerless' over compensation scheme
OL,6,FThere were also claims that the
OL,7,F"Cabinet Office seem to have
OL,8,Fobstructed progress for funding
OL,9,Freasons, seem to believe and have
OL,10,Fconsistently argued that those
OL,11,Finfected and affected do not really
OL,12,Fneed independent legal representation".
OL,14,FCharities told the inquiry of a
OL,15,Fsignificant influx of calls and emails
OL,16,Fafter the publication of the report
OL,17,Fand news of the compensation scheme.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/15
