OL,3,CInfected-blood victims 'distressed and
OL,4,Cpowerless' over compensation scheme
OL,6,FLast month, a lawyer representing
OL,7,Ffamilies and victims of the scandal
OL,8,Fclaimed only about 0.2% of potential
OL,9,Fclaimants have been invited to seek
OL,10,Fpayouts.
OL,12,FAt the time, Des Collins, whose firm
OL,13,FCollins Solicitors advised thousands
OL,14,Fof people affected, said the scheme is
OL,15,Fnot yet able to cope with "anywhere
OL,16,Fnear" the volume of applications it
OL,17,Fshould be processing.
OL,19,FHe welcomed the news that the inquiry
OL,20,Fwould be publishing a further report.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/15
