OL,3,CInfected-blood victims 'distressed and
OL,4,Cpowerless' over compensation scheme
OL,6,F"We agree that there is an urgent need
OL,7,Fto bring some transparency to the
OL,8,Fimplementation of the compensation
OL,9,Fscheme which has, to date, been a very
OL,10,Fopaque process," Mr Collins said.
OL,12,F"As far as our clients are concerned
OL,13,Fthere has been no meaningful
OL,14,Fparticipation in the development of
OL,15,Fthe scheme."
OL,17,FHe added: "Many of our clients and
OL,18,Fothers in the community are once more
OL,19,Ffed up with the patronising approach
OL,20,Fbeing adopted and have reached out to
OL,21,FSir Brian accordingly.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/15
